{
  "texts": [
    "A recent example of this involved an unfortunate American lawyer who used ChatGPT to generate a legal brief for a case in Federal District Court that, although it resembled a real brief, was filled with fake judicial opinions and legal citations (Weiser & Schweber, 2023).",
    "Furthermore, ChatGPT and other LLMs struggle with interpretation that requires topic-specific knowledge.",
    "Thus, LLMs can be used to find latent, context-dependent meanings from interviews or open-ended survey answers without any guidance, but they should not be trusted to interpret texts with specialized facts or theories.",
    "For this reason, ChatGPT requires researcher supervision and is only suitable for specific stages of the research process, as described below, and with full awareness of the critical, ethical, and environmental considerations that coincide with LLMs and other AI applications.",
    "Apart from these questions, another issue that should be considered when using computational and AI-driven technology is their impact on the environment."
  ]
}